TELEMEDICINE, TRANSATLANTIC SUMMIT - USA (BOSTON) MAY 1997
==========================================================
Transatlantic Telemedicine Summit
Hyatt Harborside Conference Center & Hotel and World Trade Center.
Boston, Mass., USA, 20-22 May 1997
----------------------------------
The Transatlantic Telemedicine Summit will bring together the international
leaders in telemedicine and related fields to respond to common concerns
and help create an action agenda to speed deployment of cost-effective
health care for all people.
Sponsored by the Atlantic Rim Network, which defines the Atlantic as "a
state of mind," it will bring together participants from both sides of the
Atlantic and as far afield as East Africa, Greece, Italy and Peru.
Participants will come from the academic, commercial and military sectors,
the White House, the World & Panamerican Health Organizations, the European
Commission, and the American, Canadian, French and Finnish societies for
telemedicine, among others.
There will be panel discussions on:
Critical issues & driving forces in telemedicine
G-7 Nations: Global health care projects
European Perspectives/ DG 13 projects
Military telemedicine perspectives
Legal/Regulatory barriers & potential solutions
Southern Hemisphere & other regional perspectives
North American perspectives
Clinical applications & market opportunities
Medical records/patient information/smart cards
Distance learning/CME/licensing & certification
Disease monitoring & management
Registration: US$895
Travel agent: Katlin Travel (617) 862-6229 Fax (617) 674-2080
For further info:
James Barron <73613.2436@compuserve.com>
OR
Jean-Pierre Thiery <symbion@mail.club-internet.fr>
